> On 3 Jul 2025, at 11:27=E2=80=AFAM, Claims <Claims@tower.co.nz =
<mailto:Claims@tower.co.nz>> wrote:
>=20
> =EF=BB=BF=20
> Good Morning Raffaella
> =20
> Thank you for your emails and apologies for the delay in responding to =
you.
> =20
> Firstly, to acknowledge the Privacy request has been received and =
passed onto our Privacy Team.
> =20
> Also acknowledging that you wish all correspondence to be via email.
> =20
> I am aware that you have met on site at your property yesterday with =
Grant Metson and that as proposed Tower will send you the documented =
process.
> =20
> In addition to this I have reviewed the information with regards to =
the expenses and can confirm the following will be paid under your =
Temporary Accommodation Benefit (limit of $30,000.00 which is the higher =
of the two policy benefits)=20
> =20
> $1,452.00            6 nights Esplanade Hotel
> $5,000.00           Rent @ $1,000.00 per week
> $727.38               Moving costs to temp accommodation
> =20
> $7,179.38           Total of Temporary Accommodation benefit used to =
date.
> =20
> The other two payments as follows will be under your Contents claim as =
part of your sum insured.
> =20
> $340                     cleaning of clothes
> $454.25               cleaning of sofa
> =20
> =20
> With regards to your query if Stress Benefit applies, unfortunately it =
only applies if the property and/or Contents is a Total Loss as per =
following policy wording, if the contents are deemed a total loss then =
we will proactively let you know of any changes to your eligibility for =
this benefit. =20
> =20
> House=20
> Stress benefit lump sum payment
> We=E2=80=99ll pay you a lump sum for the stress caused to you if your =
entire house is destroyed.
> We pay this benefit in addition to your sum insured.
> Limit
> We=E2=80=99ll pay a maximum of $1,000 for each event as soon as =
we=E2=80=99ve accepted your house claim
> =20
> Contents=20
> Stress benefit lump sum payment
> We=E2=80=99ll pay you a lump sum for the stress caused to you if all =
your contents are destroyed.
> This benefit is in addition to your contents sum insured.
> Limit
> We=E2=80=99ll pay a maximum of $2,000 for each event as soon as we =
have accepted your contents
> claim.
> =20
> Please advise if you are happy for these payments to be made to your =
nominated account on file where the premiums are deducted from or wish =
to supply an alternative account.
> =20
> Just reach out if you have any further questions as always, I am happy =
to assist.
> =20
> Kind Regards
> =20
> =20
> =20
